A vintage-style illustration of a lone software developer hunched over a cluttered wooden workbench filled with scattered mechanical gears, brass tools, and half-assembled clockwork mechanisms. The scene evokes a 19th-century inventor's workshop with warm sepia tones and soft candlelight casting dramatic shadows. In the center, an intricate puzzle box lies partially open, revealing complex interlocking pieces that refuse to fit together. Small brass nameplates and registry cards are pinned to a cork board behind the desk. A magnifying glass rests beside technical blueprints showing browser window diagrams rendered in an antiquated engineering style. The developer's expression shows determination mixed with frustration, one hand scratching their head while the other holds a tiny precision screwdriver. Dust motes float in amber light streaming through a single arched window.
